I'm Anne of All Trades. In NASHVILLE, I have a woodworking, blacksmithing and fabrication shop, a selection of furry friends, and an organic farm. Whether you've got the knowledge, tools, time or space to do the things you've always wanted to do, everything is "figureoutable." 

I became "Anne of All Trades" out of necessity. With no background in farming or making things, I wanted to learn to raise my own food, fix things when they break and build the things I need. 

12 years ago I got my first pet, planted my first seed and picked up my first tool. 

My goal is to learn and share traditional techniques and skills while showing my peers how to get from where they are to where they want to go, how to do the things they are passionate about, and what can be done TODAY to engage their own community and grow deep roots. 

Whether it's carving spoons, making my own hand tools, restoring my antique truck or growing heirloom tomatoes, the farm and workshop definitely keep me busy and support - whether financially through Patreon, through shopping my affiliate links, through buying merchandise, plans or project videos, or even just liking, commenting, and sharing my content with others helps me GREATLY to keep producing quality content to share.

Get a better roadmap of how to grow deep roots and live the life you want by subscribing to this channel and be sure to check out my blog for even more info https://anneofalltrades.com

title: PREGNANCY UPDATE: 17 WEEKS PREGNANT AND THINGS ARE CHANGING!
description:
Check out Simple below:
https://simple.life/survey/?utm_source=influencer&utm_medium=affiliate&utm_campaign=carlin&utm_ad_group_id=influencers&utm_term=imaf&ad_id=93998&utm_content=youtube&plans_type=short&safe=true

We made a quick trip to Nashville to celebrate three of my siblings’ birthdays—plus a special one for our little guy Zade, who just turned three! We soaked up the family time, cheered on our nephew at his baseball game, and enjoyed just hanging out and being together.

After heading back home, the kids jumped right into one of their favorite things—swim lessons! They’re becoming total water bugs and seriously never want to get out of the pool. It’s been so fun to watch them grow and gain confidence in the water.

Carlin also got treated to a sweet birthday outing! Her sisters surprised her with a Color Analysis, and she had the best time! It was such a fun and thoughtful gift.

We wrapped up the vlog with a little pregnancy update—Carlin is officially 17 weeks along! We chatted about her cravings, symptoms, and what we’re praying for as we get closer to meeting baby #3.

Thanks so much for being here, for supporting our fam, and for always being so kind in the comments. Make sure to like the video, subscribe, and come back next week for more life with the Stewarts!
